# .npmrc
save-exact=true
legacy-peer-deps=false
```

`save-exact=true` means every install pins to an exact version (`"18.2.0"` instead of `"^18.2.0"`), which eliminates the most common source of "works on my machine" bugs.

---

## Node version pinning

The second biggest source of issues. Pin your Node version with an `.nvmrc` file in the repo root:
```
20.11.0